<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://forums.interealms.com/ranger/showthread.php?threadid=31724">forums.interealms.com/ran...adid=31724</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Absofuckinlutely rediculous.  Rogues, Monks, even under Trueshot, a Stonewood, and 11+4 Damage arrows, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Rangers will not meet or exceed your DPS, </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> even after AM3+EQ.<br>
<br>
There has been tons of talk lately about caster DPS being higher than Melee, and I dont buy it.  Sure, that Wizard can blast the shit out of something, but, he'll also get splattered all over the zone if he does it at the wrong time.  As I said in my post on one of those threads, Ranger &quot;backstabs&quot; (Icewind, Calefaction, Brushfire...) have at least a 1.8 second cast time, in which we are not meleeing, thus, hampering DPS.  Trueshot, Harmtouch, and other Hybrid burst damage has very limited application.  Once an hour for Trueshot and Harmtouch, and slay undead...well...self explanatory.  Knights get much lower weapon skills than anyone else as well.<br>
<br>
Hybrid spells are supposed to make up for the fact that we dont excell in the areas that pure melee do.  Warriors, Monks, Rogues...you guys have to admit that these changes (other than the /disc changes, that I think are a good idea) would seriously imbalance melee to an irreparable state.<br>
<br>
In all seriousness, I hate class balance talk, for the most part, its silly.  If we were suppsoed to be balanced, everyone could nuke like a Wizard, heal like a Cleric, and tank like a Warrior.  But if these changes go live, I beleive you are going to see a lot of Rangers, Beastlords, Shadowknights, and Paladins standing around with our thumbs up our asses, because no one wants us around.<br>
<br>
Plus these aren't even working correctly  on Test server to my knowledge. Typical. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   But please /feedback about this.  It's an overall bad idea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sarhea>Sarhea</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3335<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/03 4:33 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Are other Hybrid classes as riled up about this?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>But if these changes go live, I beleive you are going to see a lot of Rangers, Beastlords, Shadowknights, and Paladins standing around with our thumbs up our asses, because no one wants us around.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
