<br>
There is nothing to be concerned about.<br>
<br>
And dude, rangers aren’t supposed to out DPS the rogues and monks. They are supposed to offer some long range support, some utility spells, and add to the damage in general. And they can track. Show me a warrior, monk, or rogue that can track.<br>
<br>
Paladins and Shadowknights are not supposed to tank every frickin thing in the game. They are supposed to act as stand-by tanks with added utility. Shadowknights are offensive utility tanks - they take away from the mob, and in higher levels give to the group. Paladins are defensive utility tanks. They like reduce damage through stuns and heal or something.<br>
<br>
End of the day though, those rogues, monks, and warriors all have one major problem, that keep us hybrids loved. Openings. They last about a tick if that much. And they appear randomly. And when tey do appear you have to have a skill loaded that can take advantage of that type of opening. And even if you meet all of these bits and pieces, the effects are a little extra damage or short duration effects. And at the moment anyway, there is a good chance that after using one, you will miss the next few openings just because the skills have timers like disciplines.<br>
<br>
Its okay. You won’t suck anymore in a week or two than you do now. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/JCOLE1/pnimages/talastiusportraitsig.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
