<br>
Rangers also have a huge advantage in that elemental bows are droppable on all servers.  Rogues and monks can't generally buy toys from Plane of Earth in the bazaar.  It's an odd itemisation decision by SOE, one we don't feel so much on FV.  But it's a big deal on the other 8434383 servers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Rangers are good damage and support/buff spells... I know for a fact that as a 60 ranger, I used to outdamage the SK I grouped with by over 50% ... (she'd do 12k during a fight, while I was already past 18k in damage) - And that was without EQ and AM3.... (in fact all I had was CF2))<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This, however, is really, really strange, unless the SK had lousy gear and the ranger had great stuff.  The ATK difference due to skill/ innate ranger bonus at that level would account for a few percentage points of DPS -- but not 50%.  SK's also get slightly better nukes, and the DPS from their pet.  All told, a 60 SK should equal or outdamage a 60 melee ranger.   This must have been one vast gear gap, a parse over a relatively short period of time, or the SK was tanking and the ranger was behind the mob.<br>
