Wrong. If the fight is the right duration, ranger + trueshot will blow a rogue away, let alone a monk. One time we were killing minis in BoT, had a high dps group, and this ranger is helping out cos he's bored. He's not in our group. He outdamaged the ENTIRE GROUP!! and accidentally killstealed the mini. Yep, it's situational. It depends on the position of the mob and the duration of the fight. Guess what? Same applies to rogues. Short duration fight we'll get outdamaged by almost any caster. Trueshot lasts two minutes, so most raid mobs where a bow can be used we'll be outdamaged by rangers. At my level at least. And monks do less damage than rogues.<br>
<br>
&quot;There has been tons of talk lately about caster DPS being higher than Melee&quot;<br>
<br>
Recently I parsed AL fight. Arch Lich has high AC, but fight was very long. The sort of fight a rogue should excel at. I was outdamaged by a wizard. Now, he has really nice gear, but all pre-elementals. I had and continue to have very few possible upgrades pre-elementals, and non that are really significant. It's a very good parse of similarly equipped pre-elemental rogue vs wizard damage. And I didn't outdamage him, on a mob which a rogue really should outdamage a wizard I feel. I guess the AC is just too high, maybe that wasn't a good mob... but in that case, what is? There aren't that many raid targets that last that long, except most of the luclin targets but then most of the luclin targets also have high AC. So what raid targets does a rogue beat a wizard on?<br>
<br>
But why should I worry. I have my uber corpse dragging abilities to fall back on.<br>
<br>
Oh but wait, rogues are scouts now! Heh... I can count the number of targets I can scout better than a ranger on 1 hand.<br>
<br>
But I can open chests in LDoN right? Nope. I swear, I don't know if I've just been really really unlucky, but I haven't found a chest I could open in literally months. (Any other rogues found this by the way? When LDoN came out, usually 1 in 2 dungeons there'd be a box for me to open, but no more. Maybe a bug?).<br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, rogues aren't hurting as bad as monks or warriors. I still churn out some nice dps. Hey, against AL I'm as important as a wizard! But rogues are below par at the moment, as it were. The next change they get needs to be a boost not a nerf.<br>
